removeBicycle(ParkingSlot) - Method in class myVelibStationNetwork.Station
This method removes a bicycle from a parking slot of the station and throws an exception if this isn't possible
removeObserver(Observer) - Method in class myVelibStationNetwork.Station
 
removeObserver(Observer) - Method in class myVelibStationNetwork.Stations
This method removes an observer from the observers lists of all the stations of StationsList.
removeObserver(Observer) - Method in interface ObserverObservableInterfaces.Observable

rentBicycle(User) - Method in class myVelibStationNetwork.UserTerminal
This method enables a user to rent a bicycle without planning the ride at the station which this is the user terminal, if there are some available bicycles there.
rentBicyclePlanningRide(User) - Method in class myVelibStationNetwork.UserTerminal
This method enables a user to rent a bicycle at the station if there is one available, in the case the trip was planned by the myvelibSystem : this means the Ride object has already been initialized and already contains the planned arrivalStation.
returnBicycle(Bicycle, MyDate) - Method in class myVelibStationNetwork.UserTerminal
This method allows a user to restore a bike to the station and most importantly to let the system know that his/her ride is over. and to know about the cost of the ride.
Ride - Class in myVelibRides
This class describes a ride between two stations of the myvelib network
Ride(PlanningRide, GPSCoordinates, GPSCoordinates, User, Class<?>) - Constructor for class myVelibRides.Ride
This constructor builds a ride that has to be planned and adds this ride to all the stations' list of observers
Ride(Station, User, Bicycle) - Constructor for class myVelibRides.Ride
This constructor builds a ride that hasn't to be planned (if the user already knows to what station he wants to go for example) and adds this ride to all the stations' list of observers
